The paper deals with the problem of estimating the value of spatio-temporal data in wholesale and retail data marketplaces, which involves data management, machine learning, and economics. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of game theory and the Shapley value, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
